message.content:
An Australian Terrier is a small breed of dog originally developed in Australia. 
They have a compact and sturdy build, with a height of around 10 to 11 inches and a weight of 14 to 16 pounds. 
Their coat is weather-resistant and typically comes in shades of blue and tan, or red. 
Their ears are erect and pointed, and they have a tail that is usually docked. 
They have a keen and energetic personality, making them good companions and watchdogs. 
Australian Terriers are commonly seen in shows and competitions, as well as in homes as pets. 
Overall, they have a distinctive and charming appearance that makes them a beloved breed among dog enthusiasts.
